            <thetext>Operating systems provide different levels of modality known as system modal (modal window blocks the entire screen, used for example for color pickers), application modal (modal window blocks all other windows of the same application), and primary modal (window blocks only its parent windows).

The qx.ui.window.Window class implements modality by placing a transparent shield between the modal window and the windows below. This approach is equivalent to system modal, but it does not allow for the other modes as it relies on a certain z-order.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
